==English==

===Noun===
'''[[wire]] [[rope]]'''

# A strong [[cable]] consisting of twisted strands of wire, generally intended for supporting heavy loads.

===Synonyms===
* [[cable]]

===Usage Note===
Although ''wire rope'' and one sense of ''cable'' are roughly synonymous, use of the term ''wire rope'' is generally restricted to applications such as hoisting and hauling, e.g. when the wire rope is used in [[elevator]]s, [[crane]]s, [[funicular]]s, [[suspension bridge]]s, or the like.